Meta Description 1: This post describes how to perform variant analysis with CodeQL to catch missing type checking in Ghostscript, leading to the discovery of 3 new type confusion vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-19134, CVE-2018-19476, CVE-2018-19477)
H1-1: Ghostscript type confusion: Using variant analysis to find vulnerabilities
H2-2: Finding type confusions with CodeQL in Ghostscript

Title 1: Swagger YAML Parser Vulnerability (CVE-2017-1000207 and CVE-2017-1000208) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Parsing YAML data from untrusted source can lead to arbitrary code execution. This post discusses a vulnerability of this type in Swagger Parser (caused by unsafe use of SnakeYaml), and shows how such vulnerabilities can be found using QL.
H1-1: Swagger YAML Parser Vulnerability (CVE-2017-1000207 and CVE-2017-1000208)
H2-1: Swagger Codegen and Swagger Parser remote code execution vulnerability (CVE-2017-1000207 and CVE-2017-1000208)

Title 1: Apple's XNU Kernel: Finding a memory exposure vulnerability with CodeQL (CVE-2017-13782) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Apple's macOS XNU kernel can be tricked into leaking sensitive kernel memory. This post describes how we can use CodeQL to find such vulnerabilities in C code.
H1-1: Apple's XNU Kernel: Finding a memory exposure vulnerability with CodeQL (CVE-2017-13782)
H2-2: About DTrace and finding this vulnerability

Title 1: CVE-2018-4259: MacOS NFS vulnerabilties lead to kernel RCE - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: A custom query, written for Apple's macOS operating system kernel, has found multiple stack and heap buffer overflows which are triggerable by connecting to a malicious NFS file server.
H1-1: CVE-2018-4259: MacOS NFS vulnerabilties lead to kernel RCE

Title 1: U-Boot NFS RCE Vulnerabilities (CVE-2019-14192) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Semmle’s security research team discovers 13 U-Boot RCE vulnerabilities in its bootloader, which is commonly used by IoT, Kindle, and ARM ChromeOS devices.
H2-2: I am using U-boot, am I affected?

Title 1: Etherpad reflected file download: Vulnerability hunting with CodeQL (CVE-2018-6835) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This blog post explains how CodeQL can be used to discover so-called 'Reflected File Download' vulnerabilities in JavaScript applications. As an example, we look at CVE-2018-6835 which we recently found in the Etherpad collaborative editor.
H1-1: Etherpad reflected file download: Vulnerability hunting with CodeQL (CVE-2018-6835)
H2-1: Details of the vulnerability in Etherpad (CVE-2018-6835)

Title 1: Restlet XML External Entity Expansion Vulnerability (CVE-2017-14868) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Unsafe parsing of user input XML data allows remote attacker arbitrary file access.
H1-1: Restlet XML External Entity Expansion Vulnerability (CVE-2017-14868)

Title 1: Insecure Deserialization: Finding Java Vulnerabilities with CodeQL - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Deserialization of untrusted data can lead to vulnerabilities that allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code. We can use CodeQL, the code query technology of LGTM, to find such deserialization vulnerabilities.
H1-1: Insecure Deserialization: Finding Java Vulnerabilities with CodeQL
H2-1: Using CodeQL to find unsafe deserialization

Title 1: Stack buffer overflow in Qualcomm MSM 4.4 - Finding bugs with CodeQL - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post describes how we can use CodeQL to find unsafe uses of copy_from_user - a C function that is used to copy data from user memory into kernel memory. When used incorrectly, it could cause a stack buffer overflow in the kernel.
H1-1: Stack buffer overflow in Qualcomm MSM 4.4 - Finding bugs with CodeQL
H2-2: Using CodeQL to find stack buffer overflows

Title 1: XXE attack example using jBoss vulnerability (jBPM) CVE-2017-7545 - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post shows how the out-of-the-box XXE query in LGTM catches an exploitable XXE vulnerability in the JBoss business process manager that is difficult to find using fuzzing or testing.
H1-1: XXE attack example using jBoss vulnerability (jBPM) CVE-2017-7545
H2-1: Details of vulnerability in JBoss Business Process Manager (jBPM)

Title 1: CVE-2018-11776: How to find 5 RCEs in Apache Struts with CodeQL - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Semmle security researcher Man Yue Mo explains how he used CodeQL's Data Flow library to discover multiple RCE vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-11776) in Apache Struts.
H1-1: CVE-2018-11776: How to find 5 RCEs in Apache Struts with CodeQL

Title 1: Apple XNU exploits: ICMP proof of concept - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: A few weeks ago, we disclosed 6 vulnerabilities in Apple's XNU operating system kernel. This post gives the details of our proof-of-concept exploits. It also explains how a query helped us find a path to the vulnerable code.
H1-1: Apple XNU exploits: ICMP proof of concept
H2-2: Client-side NFS vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-4259, CVE-2018-4286, CVE-2018-4287, CVE-2018-4288, CVE-2018-4291)

Title 1: Android Deserialization Vulnerabilities: A Brief history - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post describes some past Android deserialization vulnerabilities that exploited C++ pointers wrapped inside Java objects. Using a single query, we can find the classes responsible for them with great precision.
H1-1: Android Deserialization Vulnerabilities: A Brief history

Title 1: CVE-2018-19475: Ghostscript shell command execution in SAFER mode - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post describes how I carried out variant analysis on a vulnerability found by Google Project Zero member Tavis Ormandy and ended up with a new one.
H1-1: CVE-2018-19475: Ghostscript shell command execution in SAFER mode
H2-1: The SAFER mode sandbox in Ghostscript

Title 1: Librelp buffer overflow fix (cve-2018-1000140) - a collaboration between Adiscon and Semmle - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This is a joint blog post, from Adiscon and Semmle, about the finding and fixing of CVE-2018-1000140, a security vulnerability in librelp.
H1-1: Librelp buffer overflow fix (cve-2018-1000140) - a collaboration between Adiscon and Semmle

Title 1: Castor and Hessian java deserialization vulnerabilities - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post shows how to use the new TaintTracking library to easily identify unsafe deserialization vulnerabilities associated with the Castor and Hessian deserialization framework. In particular, two new vulnerabilities, CVE-2017-12633 and CVE-2017-12634 are discovered in Apache Camel.
H1-1: Castor and Hessian java deserialization vulnerabilities
H2-1: Apache Camel vulnerabilities CVE-2017-12633 and CVE-2017-12634
H2-2: Finding the vulnerabilities in Apache Camel

Title 1: Spring Data REST exploit (CVE-2017-8046): Finding a RCE vulnerability with CodeQL - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: The query language that forms the foundation of LGTM's code analysis makes it very easy to find new security vulnerabilities and variants of it. In this post we look at Spring Data REST, and how CodeQL helped making sure a remote code execution vulnerability was truly eradicated.
H1-1: Spring Data REST exploit (CVE-2017-8046): Finding a RCE vulnerability with CodeQL

Title 1: Exploiting CVE-2018-19134: Ghostscript RCE through type confusion - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: This post describes how I used variant analysis to develop an exploit for Ghostscript CVE-2018-19134, a type confusion vulnerability that allows arbitrary shell command execution.
H1-1: Exploiting CVE-2018-19134: Ghostscript RCE through type confusion

Title 1: Apple NFS Diskless Boot: Negative integer overflow vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-4136 & CVE-2018-4160) - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: TThis post explains how to use CodeQL to find calls to bcopy where the size argument might be negative.
H1-1: Apple NFS Diskless Boot: Negative integer overflow vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-4136 & CVE-2018-4160)

Title 1: CVE-2017-9805: How CodeQL found a remote code execution vulnerability in Apache Struts - GitHub Security Lab
Meta Description 1: Deserialization of untrusted user data caused a remote code execution vulnerability in Apache Struts. This post explains how CodeQL, LGTM's code query technology, was used to find this vulnerability.
H1-1: CVE-2017-9805: How CodeQL found a remote code execution vulnerability in Apache Struts
